if (layer.LSB < low): name = layer.parent.name comp = GSComponent(name) isAutoAligned = comp.automaticAlignment print('fix low LSB...: ', name) if isAutoAligned: for comp in layer.components: comp.setDisableAlignment_(True) print(comp) layer.LSB = newLSB
if (layer.LSB > top): name = layer.parent.name comp = GSComponent(name) isAutoAligned = comp.automaticAlignment print('fix top LSB...: ', name) if isAutoAligned: for comp in layer.components: comp.setDisableAlignment_(True) print(comp) layer.LSB = top

# Important Forum answers. https://forum.glyphsapp.com/t/font-bakery-hinting-error-message-bit-3-of-head-table/16210 kedar Oct 29 For anyone having the same issue, here’s the solution summary:
Get gftools 1
Run gftools fix-hinting font-name.ttf This will generate a file: font-name.ttf.fix
Discard the font-name.ttf file and rename font-name.ttf.fix to font-name.ttf
To automate this for multiple files, here’s a bash script:
echo "Fixing Hinting" for font in *.ttf do gftools fix-hinting $font; if [ -f "$font.fix" ]; then mv "$font.fix" $font; fi done Be sure to be inside the same folder as the *.ttf files to avoid chmod issues.

def add_base(): for layer in font.selectedLayers: layers = layer.parent.layers for lyr in layers: try: ucode = layer.parent.unicode.lower() base_name = ethiopics[ucode] part = GSComponent(base_name) if len(lyr.components) is 0: lyr.components.append(part) print('added: ', base_name, 'in ', lyr.name) else: print(base_name, ' already in this layer') except: print('error ocurred')
def cleanup(): for layer in font.selectedLayers: layers = layer.parent.layers for lyr in layers: print("cleaning ", lyr.name) if lyr.anchors: for i, a in enumerate(lyr.anchors): try: del lyr.anchors[i] except: print("no anchor at this index", i) if lyr.shapes: for i, s in enumerate(lyr.shapes): try: del lyr.shapes[i] except: print("no shape at this index", i)
def add_base_cap(cap): cleanup() for layer in font.selectedLayers: layers = layer.parent.layers for lyr in layers: base_name = cap part = GSComponent(base_name) if len(lyr.components) is 0: lyr.components.append(part) print('added: ', base_name, 'in ', lyr.name)
def add_part(part, cap): for layer in font.selectedLayers: layers = layer.parent.layers for lyr in layers: comp = GSComponent(part) key = part if cap: key = key + '.cap' exists = lyr.userData[key] print(exists) if not exists: key = part if cap: key = key + '.cap' exists = lyr.userData[key] = True lyr.components.append(comp) print('added: ', part, 'on ', layer.parent.name, lyr.name) else: print(lyr.components) print(part, ' not added xxxx')
add_part('_smart.hi', True) #add_base() #add_base_cap('la.base.cap')
